import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'], color='blue', linewidth=2)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend in net electricity generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    ax.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.pivot(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation')
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of net electricity generation across different energy sources?')
    ax.legend(title='Energy Source', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    renewable_sources = data[data['source'] == 'Renewables']
    renewable_sources_net_generation = renewable_sources['net_generation'].sum()
    non_renewable_sources = data[data['source'] != 'Renewables']
    non_renewable_sources_net_generation = non_renewable_sources['net_generation'].sum()
    labels = ['Renewables', 'Non-Renewables']
    sizes = [renewable_sources_net_generation, non_renewable_sources_net_generation]
    colors = ['#2ca02c', '#d62728']
    fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax1.pie(sizes, labels=labels, colors=colors, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax1.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the proportion of electricity generated from renewable sources?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Sources', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt;

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('source').mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['source'], data['net_generation'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c'])
    plt.title('What is the average net electricity generation for each energy source?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Energy Source')
    plt.ylabel('Average Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    plt.ylim(0, 30000)
    for i, val in enumerate(data['net_generation']):
        plt.text(i, val+1000, f"{val:.2f}", ha='center')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
